agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: 1. All studies/reports in the possession, custody or control of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and/or the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR) that scientifically prove the existence of the alleged measles virus; Note: Scientific proof is NOT • Opinions • Speculation • Review papers • Descriptive papers Scientific proof requires • Use of the scientific method • Repeatable and falsifiable hypotheses that have been tested using valid, controlled experiments where only 1 variable differs between the experimental and control groups • In this case, the 1 manipulated variable would be the presence/absence of purified particles suspected of being a "virus" • Consistent results from valid, controlled experiments (i.e. identical "genomes", consistent in vivo effects) 2. If the CDC has no studies responsive to #1 above, please indicate such explicitly, and provide all studies and/or reports in the possession, custody or control of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and/or the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR) describing the purification of particles that are alleged to be this virus, directly from bodily fluid/tissue/excrement or from a cell culture, with purification confirmed via EM imaging (the images must be available as well). Please note that I am not requesting studies/reports where researchers failed to purify the suspected "virus" and instead: • cultured an unpurified sample or other unpurified substance, and/or • performed an amplification test (i.e. a PCR test), and/or • created an in silico "genome", and/or • produced electron microscopy images of unpurified things.

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, in coordination with other federal partners, is responsible for ensuring that record keeping and reporting requirements for imported primates are followed. Specifically, at least seven days before importing a shipment of NHPs, an importer must notify HHS/CDC in writing or by email of the impending shipment and provide detailed information regarding the origin, number and species of primates, the importer’s name and address, specific itinerary details and CITES permit number and expiration date, etc. In December 2022, a U.S. animal testing company called INOTIV, released a statement saying that in the aftermath of the arrest of a Cambodian wildlife official for alleged monkey smuggling and passing off wild macaques as captive-bred ones, Cambodia has ceased exports of monkeys to the US. A separate case report was then published by the American Association for Laboratory Animal Science that month indicating that exported monkeys from that country have also had hard-to-detected melioidosis, a disease which is fatal to humans when untreated and one which has no readily available commercial test. Symptoms of the disease do not typically show up within the 31-day required U.S. quarantine period. With that in mind, it's a matter of public safety to know: how many non-human primate import shipments from Cambodia have occurred since November 17, 2022 and how many shipments are planned with filed paperwork or correspondence? Please include all relevant details about these shipments from that date until the time this request is completed, including all correspondence and filed paperwork. Please send all results electronically, not on a CD. (Date Range for Record Search: From 11/17/2022 To 01/04/2023)

request_text: To Whom It May Concern, I am writing to request information under the Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) and the applicable regulations of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). I am seeking factual evidence that the virus SARS-CoV-2 was isolated from a live infected human, as opposed to information that it was isolated from an animal or artificially introduced into someone's body. Specifically, I am requesting all documents, including but not limited to lab reports, scientific studies, and researcher's notes, that provide evidence of the isolation of SARS-CoV-2 from a live infected human. If it is determined that any portion of the requested information is exempt from disclosure, please provide me with a detailed explanation of the exemptions that apply. If my request is denied in whole or in part, please provide me with the reason for the denial, including the specific statutory exemptions relied upon. I respectfully request that you expedite the processing of this request, as it concerns a matter of significant public interest. Thank you for your attention to this matter.

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Through this request, I would like to obtain a listing of site locations that are, known to be or suspected to be, contaminated with PFAS chemicals, for the entire United States, in spreadsheet format. PFAS is a class of chemicals that includes PFOA (perfluorooctanoic acid), PFOS (perfluorooctanesulfonic acid), PFNA (perfluorononanoic acid) and PFHxA (perfluorohexanoic acid). PFOA and PFOS, are the most commonly found and potent PFASs at contamination sites. ATSDR is involved at a number of PFAS-related sites, either directly or through assisting state and federal partners. As of now, most sites are related to drinking water contamination connected with PFAS production facilities or fire training areas where aqueous film-forming firefighting foam (AFFF) was regularly used. We are working with one state partner on a site where consuming contaminated fish is the concern. Information I would like includes: Region contact information: Contact name Contact title Contact phone number Contact fax number Contact email address Site information: Site name Site location address Site location city Site location state Site location zip code Latitude Longitude Detail information Contaminant information: PFAS substance Source of contamination Media affected

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Any records in the possession, custody or control of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and/or the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry for SARS-COV-2 recorded under an Optical Nanoscope at Super Resolution (SMAL). Optical Nanoscopes can rapidly record images that are stitched together to produce sub 100nm resolution images. SARS-COV-2 is alleged to be between 30nm to 150nm in size; therefore, an optical nanoscope should easily be able to capture the allusive virus. Furthermore, an optical nanoscope should be able to capture SARS-COV-2 invading cells, replicating, and bursting out of living cells as is claimed by virologists. NO Electron Micrographs Do not include any records of Electron Micrographs because the process of making an electron micrograph creates artifacts that are indistinguishable from the subject matter. Electron Micrographs are simply unreliable and outdated technology compared to Optical Nanoscopes. Summary Please provide any records of optical nanoscope images (SMAL) of SARS-COV-2 as defined in this request. If any records match the above description of requested records and are currently available to the public elsewhere, please provide enough information about each record so that I may identify and access each one with certainty (i.e. title, author(s), date, journal, where the public may access it). Please provide URLs where possible.

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: I want to analyze HPV vaccination administration rates at the county level using data collected by the Immunization Information Systems (IIS). IIS distills vaccination for individuals at the population level for surveillance and program evaluation. When I inquired about the availability of IIS data aggregated at the county level, Ms. Kingerly told me that the Freedom of Information Act unit provided information about proposals and contractual agreements required for academic analysis with these data. We want to evaluate associations between HPV vaccination and community-level measures of social determinants of health. The PLACES (CDC) and County Health Rankings and Roadmaps (RWJF) projects are examples of county-level data that could uncover predictors of vaccination adherence when merged with county-level IIS files. I would appreciate your agency's advice about the feasibility of applying for a restricted data set for analysis purposes using a data use agreement between my university and the CDC. Thank you for your time and consideration, and I look forward to your response.

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: This office represents Thomson International, Incorporated (“Thomson”) in Bakersfield, California. On August 1, 2020, Thomson voluntarily recalled red, yellow, white, and sweet yellow onions shipped from May 1, 2020 through August 1, 2020. Thomson red onions are allegedly a probable source of a Salmonella Newport outbreak in the U.S. and Canada in summer 2020. 1. All publicly-available records relating to any reported illness of b6, b6 and b6, including but not limited to correspondence, investigative reports, medical records, laboratory test results, epidemiological records and Whole Genomic Sequencing (“WGS”) ID related to b6 [WGS ID: b6], b6 [WGS ID: b6], b6. 2. All records relating to your investigation of Thomson as a potential source of Salmonella Newport outbreak in 2020. 3. All records relating to the WGS of Salmonella Newport outbreak in 2020. 4. All records detailing potential sources of Salmonella Newport outbreak in 2020. 5. All of your traceback records relating to the Salmonella Newport outbreak in 2020. 6. All records detailing potential sources of Salmonella Newport outbreak tied to onions in 2020. 7. All records detailing your investigative procedures for identifying sources of foodborne illnesses reported to you that were used to identify the source of foodborne illnesses reported in 2020. 8. All records relating to efforts to continue investigating foodborne illnesses after a potential source is identified that were part of your procedures for foodborne illness outbreaks in 2020. 9. All statistics and/or other measures for testing accuracy of identified sources of foodborne illnesses that were part of your procedures for foodborne illnesses outbreaks in 2020. 10. All records relating to procedures for determining genetic matches for potential foodborne illnesses that were part of your procedures for foodborne illness outbreaks in 2020. 11. All Salmonella positive sampling and testing results, including the specific location, related to the outbreak investigation for Salmonella Newport in onions that was linked to Thomson in 2020.

request_text: This office is in the process of investigating the Tuberculosis outbreak at the Stafford Creek Correctional Center in Aberdeen, Washington. Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, please provide us with complete and accurate copies of the following: 1. Any and all policies, procedures, reporting requirements, or any other material regarding Tuberculosis testing, screening, monitoring, isolation, and treating for Washington State Department of Corrections; 2. All communications (Written and electronic) between CDC and Washington State Department of Corrections, Stafford Creek Correctional Center, Washington State Department of Health, and/or Grays Harbor County Public Health and Social Services Department regarding Tuberculosis from January 1, 2019 to present; 3. Any and all reports or complaints regarding Tuberculosis in Washington State prisons from January 1, 2019 to present; 4. All inspections, notes, reports and any other material or documents from January 1, 2019 to present of Stafford Creek Correctional Center in Aberdeen, Washington regarding Tuberculosis; 5. All emergency event evaluations, inspections, notes, reports, and any other material or documents from January 1, 2019 to present from all Washington State Correctional facilities regarding Tuberculosis; 6. All records, notes, reports, and any other material or documents regarding inspections conducted in accordance with Infectious Disease outbreaks at Washington State Correctional facilities, including but not limited to Stafford Creek Correctional Center in Aberdeen, Washington from January 1, 2019 to present for Tuberculosis; 7. All reports, notes, records, and any other materials or documents regarding Tuberculosis contact tracing within all Washington State Correctional facilities between January 1, 2019 to present; 8. All reports, notes, records, and any other material or documents regarding the transfer of inmates within Washington State Department of Corrections between January 1, 2019 to presents of Tuberculosis positive of suspected Tuberculosis positive inmates; and 9. Any and all other documents, notes, communications, records, materials, and/o reports, in CDC’s possession regarding Tuberculosis at Stafford Creed Correctional Center in Aberdeen, Washington from January 1, 2019 to present.

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Due to research work in the field of vaccination side effects, I use the VAERS data sets for the region of Germany and the EU. Since November 18, 2022, the research options of the Non-Domestic Data Set have been restricted to such an extent that a national assignment of cases in the EU area is no longer possible. It is also no longer possible to filter the data by manufacturer of the vaccines. This restriction goes far beyond the protection of patient data. In the disclaimer at the VAERS Data Sets-page (https://vaers.hhs.gov/data/datasets.html?) , it is written that due to a request of European regulators, CDC and FDA have removed certain data fields (country codes; reported symptom case narrative free text; diagnostic laboratory data free text field; illness at time of vaccination free text field; chronic conditions free text medical history field; allergies free text field) from foreign VAERS reports. I have the following questions for the CDC: - Which European regulator initiated these censorship measures? - Which national or international laws or European regulations not comply with the published data? - Can you send me copies of the request of European regulators (emails, documents, meeting notes or related attorney correspondence)? I would be very grateful if you could answer my questions promptly. Best regards Stefan Schoeneich (Date Range for Record Search: From 07/01/2022 To 02/07/2023)

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Under the Georgia Open Records Act § 50.18.70 et seq., I am requesting an opportunity to inspect or obtain copies of public records that explain in detail each of the specific ingredients dispensed in each of the four different COVID-19 vaccines. I am requesting this information under the United States Code 42, Chapter 6A Public Health Service, Subchapter XIX Vaccines. Information can be found on the CDC website regarding what is NOT included in the vaccines, but what is specifically included is not made accessible to the public. As it is important to know what is not included in the vaccines for medical purposes, it is equally as important to know what is included to give the public full transparency on what is going inside their bodies. The only information of the contents that are mentioned on your website is that "nearly all ingredients in COVID-19 Vaccines are ingredients found in foods- fats, sugar, and salts." It says that these are "nearly" all the "ingredients" used. What are the others not included in that list? This is information given to direct citizens away from knowing what is specifically included in the ingredients. If all of the ingredients are in daily food, then a specific list of what all is dispensed into the vaccine should be included as well. If the information is classified, then administering the vaccine with unknown ingredients is unjust. Vaccine Information Statements (VISs) are required to be given by Federal Law to patients receiving a COVID-19 vaccine by healthcare staff. These VISs should include the specific ingredients included in the vaccine to fall under the Federal Law requirement.

All studies/reports in the possession, custody or control of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and/or the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR) that scientifically prove the existence of the alleged herpes virus (herpes simplex virus type 1 (HSV-1) and herpes simplex virus type 2 (HSV-2); Note: Scientific proof is NOT • Opinions • Speculation • Review papers • Descriptive papers Scientific proof requires • Use of the scientific method • Repeatable and falsifiable hypotheses that have been tested using valid, controlled experiments where only 1 variable differs between the experimental and control groups • In this case, the 1 manipulated variable would be the presence/absence of purified particles suspected of being a "virus" • Consistent results from valid, controlled experiments (i.e. identical "genomes", consistent in vivo effects) 2. If the CDC has no studies responsive to #1 above, then please indicate such explicitly, and provide all studies and/or reports in the possession, custody or control of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and/or the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR) describing the purification of particles that are alleged to be this virus, directly from bodily fluid/tissue/excrement or from a cell culture, with purification confirmed via EM imaging (the images must be available as well). Please note that I am not requesting studies/reports where researchers failed to purify the suspected "virus" and instead: • cultured an unpurified sample or other unpurified substance, and/or • performed an amplification test (i.e. a PCR test), and/or • created an in silico "genome", and/or • produced electron microscopy images of unpurified things.

request_text: I am seeking … 1. … East Palestine Incident Reports, memos, and other documents created by ATSDR on or around March 6, with content that describes, but are not limited to, activities, observations, symptoms, and illnesses of the ACE team members. locations during their time in East Palestine before and during the onset of their illnesses, (b) documents that prove the ATSDR conducted a formal post-exposure medical evaluation for these employees (names, personal info redacted). 3. …documents that describe exposure symptoms reported, to include, but are not limited to, nausea, headaches, etc. 4. …documents and correspondence pertaining to Captain Shugart or other ATSDR employees notifying Incident Commander USEPA, which may include, but is not limited to, Region 5 On Scene Coordinator Ralph Dollhopf and persons similar. 5. …documents showing that ATSDR notified OSHA and NIOSH about these potential injuries and asked these agencies technical assistance and advice about PPE needed for the next East Palestine deployment. 6. …documents that describe why and when the ATSDR would be halting their investigation due to their employee safety concerns on and around March 6. 7. …a copy of the site safety plan ATSDR prepared for the field investigation, and the explanation of personal protective equipment (PPE) donned by ATSDR employees onsite. 8. …documents denoting the occupations of the ACE team members in East Palestine March 6, which could be but are not limited to physicians, nurses, health specialists, epidemiologists, etc. 9. …documents describing when ATSDR halted the onsite ACE team work on or around March 7. 10. …communications between ACE team members, other ATSDR employees, other government agencies, and contractors about this issue. 11. …communications between the ATSDR and USEPA pertaining to the detectors or PIDs inside homes by ATSDR employees, USEPA employees, or their contractors. 13. …communications to and from ATSDR pertaining to the USEPA TAGA bus being unable to detect chemicals of agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: An outbreak of E. coli O121:H19 was investigated by the CDC, FDA, and state partners. This outbreak has been linked to Earth Grown frozen falafel manufactured by Cuisine Innovations. On October 7, Whole Genome Sequencing done at the Michigan Department of Health & Human Services showed that the E. coli strain in the falafel sample was closely related to the strain causing illness in this outbreak. As of December 1, 2022, CDC announced that the outbreak is over. There was a total of 24 illnesses in six states. Marler Clark Law Firm represents clients who fell ill in this outbreak. We are writing to request copies of any records on file at the FDA, compiled between October 2022 and today, regarding the investigation of this outbreak. We specifically request: • summary reports (NORS reports and/or slides) of any investigation done for this outbreak, including the final number of cases and information regarding the suspected source; • a most current linelist of all cases considered a part of the outbreak); • any WGS analyses conducted on cases included in the outbreak (phylogenetic trees with WGS IDs); and • any traceback information regarding the sources associated with this outbreak.
